April is Sexual Assault Awareness Month, as a a Survivor and member of @rainn Leadership Council advocacy has been a huge apart of both my professional and personal life. 

Every 68 seconds an American is Sexually Assaulted. 1 - 6 children are sexually assaulted by the time they are 17 and more likely to revictimized in life as an adult than someone who did not experience sexual violence as a child. 94% of survivors have PTSD, with over 30% contemplating suicide and over 13% that have attempted suicide. 

I shared my story publicly and created a short film called “Grummy” based on my own childhood experiences (both of which are in my the highlights of my bio), in hopes to others would feel less alone and spread awareness on CSA. 

@vixen_by_micheline_pitt has raised and donated over $30K to @rainn that has helped over 3.7 million survivors and their loved ones, and is the only 24/7 hotline for Sexual Abuse survivors in the USA. All profits from @vixen_by_micheline_pitt collection of RAINN shirts are donated annually to @rainn, click the link in my bio to grab one in sizes XS - 4X now. 🖤 #VixenNotaVictim #survivor #RAINN #SAAPM #Grummy #vixenbymichelinepitt

7 years ago this last April I started @vixen_by_micheline_pitt.

I was so busy with two full time jobs and deadlines this April to even think about putting a post together. As I reflect on where my career is now and the projects ahead, I am reminded of where it began. Everything has come full circle it feels like.

I started @vixen_by_micheline_pitt with my own artwork and original designs. Two of my first novelty prints and most of my products celebrated my love of makeup. Especially red lipstick, which led to an amazing opportunity to collaborate on some incredible makeup products with one of my favorite lipstick brands @juliehewettla in 2017. 

I was working out of a tiny 1 bedroom apartment and shipping orders out of a storage space. I taped hot pink paper to the wall of my tiny apartment, (which I had to rearrange just to do this) with a cheap happy snap camera and some little LED lights I bought as Fry’s in Burbank. I worked day and night doing everything, from designing, packing orders, customer service, and production. I was a one woman show, in the very beginning, I had some friends who could come help on hard days which I was grateful to be able to pay. 

It all started with a drawing, an idea, and a dream, and 7 years later I never stopped dreaming. Looking forward to sharing what is to come in the future. 💄 #vixenbymichelinepitt #redlipstick #makeup

I know our experience is not everyone’s experience, and I know we may not be as lucky in the future. 

My biggest fear of all of this which I feel like isn’t getting talked about enough is how Hollywood for the first time is actually becoming a diverse and inclusive space for so many voices, that are at risk with Ai technology. 

I can’t imagine a computer writing about what it is like to be a woman, an abuse survivor, a person of color or a queer person. A computer can not experience life, and can not tell our stories. The streamers and studios rejected our efforts to protect writers work from Ai completely and I hope you all paying attention to what is happening. #WGA #ScreenWriter #WGAStrike

@lynhhaaga and I worked on this collection over the last year.

Using fabrics designed to handle hotter climates, made heavily of rayon, breathable, comfortable and sensory friendly. 

We wanted this to be less formal and consisting of styles you could dress up or down, with flexible fits where ever possible. 

We also created a new bag and a beautiful authentic reproduction of the iconic Victorian hand belt that was popular in the 1800’s and had a resurgence of popularity in the 1970’s. This specific belt with the full 3D hands on front and back are extremely rare, and very expensive. So we love making something old, new again to be more accessible to others. It is made of brass, comes in 3 plate finishes and uses the same authentic materials they used in the 1800s to the 1970s featuring the snap adjustable function. 

Shop the entire line in sizes XS - 4X now exclusively at @la_femme_en_noir_. 🖤 #lafemmeennoir #gothicglamour #cottagewitch

I remember @lynhhaaga and I spending months and thousands of dollars on molds and samples to make a pumpkin bag unlike anyone’s bag on the market.

After getting our very first studio collaboration, being such a small indie brand working out of our homes and small work space it felt like such a huge accomplishment. We were so proud of what we created in 2019.

I sculpted the face myself to get it as close to the pumpkin from the Sleepy Hollow film so we could have something to mold. I remember getting that first sample in and how excited we were that all that money and time in development had finally paid off.

This bag became a staple in our brand @la_femme_en_noir_, so much the studio continued to renew our deal every year, and we introduced our mini pumpkin bag. 

Both of these are in-stock and ready to ship exclusively at @la_femme_en_noir_, so if you want to support a small indie POC female owned brand, snag one today! @lynhhaaga and I put our heart and souls into everything we create to take care of our small amazing team and our families.

Jim Henson was my hero growing up.

As children we escape into worlds where we discover joy, imagination, and wonder. Labyrinth was one of those films where I discovered all of those things. I dreamt of found family and adventures unknown with a big furry beast. I watched that VHS tape so many times, I listened to the songs on repeat, and lost myself in the incredible art of Brian Froud. 

Now as an adult to have the immense pleasure and honor to make this collection with @hensoncompany for @vixen_by_micheline_pitt over the last year. I also got to work with one of my favorite artists @iriscompiet and showcase her stunning work from the “Jim Henson’s Labyrinth Bestiary” book on several clothing pieces. Iris’s work lends itself so beautifully to these pieces, and it is so amazing that others will get to wear and celebrate her work all over the world through this collection. The collection released today, so many pieces have been met with so much joy and excitement, I couldn’t help but cry after our live stream today. 

As a designer we can feel like our work is an extension of who we are as people, and our self worth is so entwined into what we create for the world. Those rare moments like todays release, I will remember for a very long time.

I want to take a moment to thank our team that helped me make this shoot possible, especially @lynhhaaga and @pattycakeflores who constantly help me create the magic that all of us get to wear and enjoy. I also have to thank our entire Vixen team who always makes coming to our HQ office such a magical experience, you all collectively make going to work feel like spending time with friends.

So proud of the collection we put together, we can’t wait until things land so that other fellow fans can enjoy their love collectively for this beautiful film.

My clown kitchen.

Our house is pretty dark and spooky, but I loved the original 1920’s Malibu tile in our kitchen. It is a mixture of soft pinks, yellows and a Tiffany blue.

The tiles themselves have lots of imperfections but the history is hard to not hold onto. We had it regrouted, I restored the hardware, repainted and repaired the original cabinets. Though it isn’t without its flaws this kitchen is almost all original, even down to the flooring. 

We even restored the same stove that was installed when the house was built almost 100 years ago. 🖤 #malibutile #vintagekitchen #vintagetile #historickitchen #historichome #vintagehome #vintagestove #NormanHauntedHome
